Package myTest

Class MapAdapterTest

java.lang.Object
myTest.MapAdapterTest
public class MapAdapterTest extends Object
This class is a test suite designed for testing the MapAdapter class.
This test suite is designed using Junit version 4.13.2, the jar files (junit-4.13.2.jar and hamcrest-core-1.3.jar) can be found in the JUnit folder.
MapAdapterTest is built as part of the exam of the course "Elementi di Ingegneria del Software" 2023/24 at Padua University.
This test suite contains n different tests plus one helper method written to avoid duplicating code. Every method of MaAdapter, EntryAdapter and private class SetAdapter is tested. Some methods could not have a test named after them, but every method is tested. The naming convention chosen is testFeatureBeingTested like.
See Also:
  • MapAdapter
  • MapAdapter.EntryAdapter
  • MapAdapter.SetAdapter
TestSuiteDesign:
For every (public) method present in the tested classes, all the possible use cases were considered and all the relevant edge cases were tested (at least these were the intentions). For example the method get could be called on an empty map, and if called on a full map than it should work and return key and should not work for negative or biggest size() indexes.

    • helper

      private MapAdapter helper(int first, int last)
      Returns a MapAdapter containing element with the keys (Integer) between first (inclusive) and last(exclusive) in order and the value the corresponding alphabet letter/s. This is a helper method, not a test.
      Parameters:
      first - the first number to be contained in the list
      last - the first number not to be contained in the list
      Returns:
      a MapAdapter containing all the keys and letters between first and last
